# Powerstone sort
A script pack that can sort(or shuffle) your powerstones, making them look better.

## Requirements
3 script and 22 max line.

[Turbo exec v2](https://github.com/Xenos6666/TPT2_scripts/tree/main/common/turbo_exec) if you have the turbo setting on.

## Config
This script allows editing the config script `sort.config` for custom effect. Here is a list of all settings available.

**`priority.[element]`**

Located on line 4-12. You need to rearrange of them instead of editing them to change the priority of the elements.

**Do not** move them out of line 4-12, this may cause unintended behavior.

The earlier an element appear in the script, the higher priority it is, and therefore powerstone of its element will be arranged earlier in the powerstone grid.

The default order follow the order elements appear in the stats to the left of the powerstone grid.

**`use turbo v2`(default `1`)** 

Whether or not to use turbo v2.

Any non-0 integer: Use turbo v2.

0: Don't use turbo v2.

**`tier priority`(default `1`)**

Any positive integer: Powerstones of the same element are ordered from **lowest** tier to **highest** tier.

0: **Ignore** powerstone tier when sorting.

Any negative integer: Powerstones of the same element are ordered from **highest** tier to **lowest** tier.

**`color priority`(default `1`)**

Any non-0 integer: Arrange powerstone based on their color and `priority.[element]` above.

0: Ignore powerstone color. `priority.[element]` setting would have no effect in this case.

Note that if both `tier priority` and `color priority` is at `0`, the script would just shuffle the powerstone, since everything is considered the same priority.

## Trivia
This script runs the known [Quicksort](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quicksort) algorithm on your powerstone list.

However, as Quicksort has a bad worst-case performance, in some rare cases the script would run so slow that it triggers the turbo exec anti-freeze function, which would prevent the script from further lagging the game.

If it happen to you, running the script again helps.
